# Human Rights Case Summary

## Slug  
human-rights-case-summary

## Description  
This skill enables summarization, analysis, and research of human rights case summaries. It supports identifying key facts, legal issues, holdings, reasoning, dissents, remedies, and broader impacts. Triggers include terms related to human rights litigation, case summaries, judgments, and legal analyses. Designed for litigation contexts with case documents and summaries.

## Metadata

| Field           | Value                         |
|-----------------|-------------------------------|
| Practice Areas  | Litigation                    |
| Document Types  | Summary                      |
| Skill Modes     | Summarization, Analysis, Research |
| Jurisdictions   | US, International Bodies     |

## Purpose Statement  
Provide clear and concise summaries of human rights cases to support legal analysis and research.

## Prerequisites  

1. Basic understanding of human rights law  
2. Familiarity with legal case structures  
3. Ability to interpret legal reasoning and holdings  
4. Awareness of relevant jurisdictions and international bodies

## Guidelines  

- Do summarize key elements following the structured template.  
- Avoid inserting unverified citations; mark uncertain references with [VERIFY].  
- Include jurisdictional context, especially US and international bodies.  
- Use concise language for clarity and precision.  
- Do not include verbose background information unrelated to legal issues.  
- Ensure summaries are balanced and factual.  
- Cite sources cautiously; placeholders are preferred when unsure.  
- Review for compliance with jurisdiction-specific rules.

## Executive Summary (Optional)  

Provide a brief overview capturing the case’s essence, holdings, and significance.

## Structured Template Sections  

| Section           | Description                                                         |
|-------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Case ID           | Unique identifier or reference for the case                         |
| Instruments       | Relevant treaties, laws, or instruments applied                     |
| Facts             | Key facts and background relevant to the case                       |
| Procedure         | Procedural history and court progression                            |
| Issues            | Legal questions the case addresses                                  |
| Holdings          | Court’s decisions on the issues                                     |
| Reasoning         | Judicial rationale supporting the holdings                          |
| Dissents          | Summary of dissenting opinions if any                               |
| Remedies          | Remedies or relief granted                                          |
| Implementation    | How the decision was or can be implemented                           |
| Impact            | Broader legal, social, or policy implications                      |
| Precedential Value| The case’s authority as precedent                                  |
| Open Questions    | Outstanding or unresolved legal questions                           |
| Sources           | References and citations (use placeholders or [VERIFY] if uncertain)|

## Verification Checklist  

- Confirm accuracy and relevance of facts and holdings.  
- Verify applicable instruments and legal frameworks.  
- Check for jurisdictional compliance.  
- Ensure reasoning aligns with case texts.  
- Review dissents and remedies for completeness.  
- Confirm impact and precedential notes are supported.  
- Mark or remove uncertain citations.

## Additional Notes  

- This skill supports cases primarily from the US jurisdiction and recognized international human rights bodies.  
- Adapt summaries according to jurisdictional nuances and legal standards.
